    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1"/> 
            
            <p>Rev. S. Morais<lb/>
                546 N. 5th St.<lb/>
                City<lb/></p>
            
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>Philad&#44; Jan 4&#47;84<lb/></p>
            <p>Rev. S. Morais<lb/></p>
            <p>Esteemed Sir<lb/></p>
            <p>The next meeting<lb/> of the Teachers&#39; Association<lb/> will be held on Monday<lb/> Evening Jan. 7th. at the Rooms<lb/> of the Y M H. A.<lb/></p>
            <p>We beg leave to submit the<lb/> following questions for<lb/> explanation&#58;<lb/></p>
            <p>&#91;Hebrew&#44; in pencil&#93;<lb/>
                1st. Did the Israelites observe<lb/> the festivals and holidays&#44; as<lb/> set forth in the 23rd Chap. of<lb/> Leviticus&#44; during their wanderings<lb/> <hi rend="underline">in the desert</hi>&#63;  If <hi rend="underline">not&#44; why not</hi>&#63;<lb/>
                2. What evidence have we that<lb/> the 1st day of Tishri is the anni&#45;<lb/><hi rend="underline">versary of the Creation</hi>&#63;<lb/></p>
            
            <pb n="3"/>
            <p>3rd. Please explain what the<lb/> cities of Refuge were&#44; and<lb/> whether they were even used<lb/> <hi rend="underline">for the purpose intended</hi>&#63;<lb/>
                &#91;Hebrew&#44; in pencil&#93;<lb/>
                4th. What ceremonies were<lb/> observed by the Israelites<lb/> at the time of New Moon&#63;&#45;&#45;<lb/>
                &#91;Hebrew&#44; in pencil&#93;<lb/>
                Please explain why we have<lb/> it at times for two days&#63;<lb/>
                &#91;Hebrew&#44; in pencil&#93;<lb/>
                5th. How were the &#34;Holy<lb/> Convocations&#34; conducted.&#45;&#45;<lb/>
                &#91;Hebrew&#44; in pencil&#93;<lb/>
                Did the Jews ever kneel<lb/> when praying.&#63; &#91;Hebrew&#44; in pencil&#93;<lb/>
                Thanking you very sincerely for<lb/> your kindness<lb/> I am<lb/> Very Respectfully<lb/> David Hoffman<lb/> <hi rend="underline">Pres</hi>.<lb/></p>
            
        </body>
